<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="126" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1436</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-06">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>179. Believe Italian Government inclined to think German order
                                declaring war zone about British Isles threatening neutral vessels
                                requires some observations. Am informally asked what our Government
                                proposes to do. This believed to be with view of having [action] on
                                parallel lines.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>